&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: And once you lose that skill,
it's really hard to get it back.

00:31:14.660 --> 00:31:19.650
And the believe it or not the most important
thing to have for skinning a squirrel is good,

00:31:19.650 --> 00:31:21.580
good boots.

00:31:21.580 --> 00:31:25.280
Because you have to hold, once you get the
skin going, you've gotta hold it and I've

00:31:25.280 --> 00:31:28.299
actually skinned a squirrel with these very
boots.

00:31:28.299 --> 00:31:31.490
Is it's a, it's a pulling thing and once you
get the, the tail meat down you get a hold

00:31:31.490 --> 00:31:34.570
of the skin and you pull it off, so you're
left with skin.

00:31:34.570 --> 00:31:38.750
&gt;&gt;Jeff Freburg: I was gonna ask what your
favorite go to meal is after this.

00:31:38.750 --> 00:31:40.150
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: My, my favorite go to meal?

00:31:40.150 --> 00:31:41.150
&gt;&gt;Jeff Freburg: Yeah.

00:31:41.150 --> 00:31:42.430
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: I've got a lot of favorite
go to meals.

00:31:42.430 --> 00:31:43.430
You know what?

00:31:43.430 --> 00:31:52.240
When in, when in doubt [pause] I, I, I have
this one, one dish that I, I really adore

00:31:52.240 --> 00:31:56.850
that I cook a lot when like my family is not
there and it's, I do this on a panini press

00:31:56.850 --> 00:31:58.170
and it's really cool.

00:31:58.170 --> 00:32:01.790
I get my panini press hot, I take three, and
by the way I don't have an endorsement from

00:32:01.790 --> 00:32:02.790
a panini press.

00:32:02.790 --> 00:32:06.250
I put three big rashers of bacon in it and
I close the lid and I wait about two minutes

00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:08.000
and let the bacon cook till it's crisp.

00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:09.000
Take it out.

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:13.250
During the time that that's out, I cut up
an onion and I cut up some mushrooms.

00:32:13.250 --> 00:32:17.530
So what I do is I take the bacon out and while
the bacon fat is in there, I throw the sliced

00:32:17.530 --> 00:32:21.130
mushrooms in, close the lid, cook another
two minutes till they're crispy, take those

00:32:21.130 --> 00:32:26.179
out, throw in some sliced onion, still enough
fat to cook, a couple of minutes, take that

00:32:26.179 --> 00:32:29.130
out, in the meantime I cut up the bacon and
then the last thing I do is I throw in two

00:32:29.130 --> 00:32:30.890
big handfuls of spinach.

00:32:30.890 --> 00:32:31.970
Baby spinach.

00:32:31.970 --> 00:32:36.650
Close the lid, count to 12, take it out, put
that all in a bowl, put some hot sauce on

00:32:36.650 --> 00:32:37.650
it and eat it.

00:32:37.650 --> 00:32:38.790
I love that.

00:32:38.790 --> 00:32:41.480
So it's a hot spinach, mushroom, bacon salad.

00:32:41.480 --> 00:32:44.260
That's kind of my, I love that meal.

00:32:44.260 --> 00:32:45.260
And canned sardines.

00:32:45.260 --> 00:32:46.370
I got a thing for sardines.

00:32:46.370 --> 00:32:47.610
&gt;&gt;Jeff Freburg: Ok.

00:32:47.610 --> 00:32:49.760
So what was the last meal that you cooked
at home?

00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:54.169
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: The last meal that I cooked
at home before I went on, on this book tour

