For two reasons: One, no one will feed you
as well as somebody who loves you.

00:33:04.860 --> 00:33:05.860
&gt;&gt;Jeff Freburg: That's true.

00:33:05.860 --> 00:33:06.860
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: I believe that.

00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:12.200
I believe there's a tangible transferable
value of, of, love in cooking for people,

00:33:12.200 --> 00:33:15.470
so I want to cook for her everyday, number
one I know I can put good nutrition on the

00:33:15.470 --> 00:33:20.919
plate and I want her to see that her dad is
there cooking for her and doing that for her,

00:33:20.919 --> 00:33:23.030
so that was my, my last meal, 'cause after
that I

