00:35:08.849 --> 00:35:13.289
site like that that you can access their recipes,
that can be quality, but just searching?

00:35:13.289 --> 00:35:14.289
Nah.

00:35:14.289 --> 00:35:17.079
&gt;&gt;male #4: So, so the ways in which that paid
service can provide you with those quality

00:35:17.079 --> 00:35:22.259
recipes that you can't find on the open internet,
which ways could we perhaps improve Google

00:35:22.259 --> 00:35:26.650
search to provide better access to higher
quality content?

00:35:26.650 --> 00:35:31.059
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: Well, you could, you could
have curators, for instance.

00:35:31.059 --> 00:35:37.880
You could have like here are Alton Brown,
here are Anthony Bourdain's 125 favorite internet

00:35:37.880 --> 00:35:38.880
recipes.

00:35:38.880 --> 00:35:42.920
Or you know you could find a way to curate
collections, you know, allowing you to package

00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:47.630
what you don't actually own, which of course
is the way of the future.

00:35:47.630 --> 00:35:48.630
[laughter]

00:35:48.630 --> 00:35:51.140
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: But the problem with, with
a recipe is you gotta have a quantifier.

00:35:51.140 --> 00:35:57.019
And a quantifier usually comes in, in the
form of the dreaded forum, which I think is

00:35:57.019 --> 00:36:01.220
the whole idea of user feedback in forum style
is pretty much, if there is anything that

00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:04.369
will ultimately destroy the usefulness of
the internet, it's that.

00:36:04.369 --> 00:36:08.430
