00:36:20.509 --> 00:36:24.630
There, there might be a way that you could
set up search strings in such a way that you

00:36:24.630 --> 00:36:32.569
could weed out a lot of things or you could
simply start getting people to go through

00:36:32.569 --> 00:36:36.119
a huge amount of print matter and, and, and
use that.

00:36:36.119 --> 00:36:39.789
You know like anything that's in public domain,
you guys have snarfed up all that stuff anyway,

00:36:39.789 --> 00:36:40.789
right?

00:36:40.789 --> 00:36:44.599
But like Mrs. Beeton's cookbooks from the
1900s, you know, maybe being able to search

00:36:44.599 --> 00:36:47.170
through that, that kind of print matter.

00:36:47.170 --> 00:36:48.190
Stuff that's actually been tested.

00:36:48.190 --> 00:36:52.269
But I, that's, that's a good, that's a conversation
probably for well it's a longer conversation

00:36:52.269 --> 00:36:54.109
figuring out how to actually do that.

00:36:54.109 --> 00:36:58.000
