easier to find one of my own recipes by just

00:37:11.029 --> 00:37:14.779
Googling it rather than going to FoodNetwork.com
and looking for it.

00:37:14.779 --> 00:37:18.359
Because I can't find it on FoodNetwork.com
unless I go through Google.

00:37:18.359 --> 00:37:24.660
So if I, if I go to Google and I type in Good
Eats meatloaf, ok, that'll actually take me

00:37:24.660 --> 00:37:29.960
someplace that I wanna go and it'll, and it,
but the nice thing would be is like if, if

00:37:29.960 --> 00:37:34.009
you went to, ok say that it is my meatloaf
recipe and you had to search this ok, Alton

00:37:34.009 --> 00:37:37.290
Brown meatloaf or Good Eats meatloaf, goes
to there, being able to have some kind of

00:37:37.290 --> 00:37:41.849
service that would then offer, hey if you
like this one, try these, in which case you

