00:56:30.759 --> 00:56:34.039
but I don't want big bubbles that look like
something that came out of a dying fish's

00:56:34.039 --> 00:56:35.039
gills.

00:56:35.039 --> 00:56:36.039
[laughter]

00:56:36.039 --> 00:56:37.859
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: You know I just don't and you
can tell me that you filled them with smoke

00:56:37.859 --> 00:56:40.809
and that it's made with blah, blah and I'm
just still, I still just don't freaking want

00:56:40.809 --> 00:56:42.769
it man, you know it's just not what I eat
ok?

00:56:42.769 --> 00:56:45.369
It, I don't have a very sophisticated palette.

00:56:45.369 --> 00:56:48.479
I like simple foods that taste like what they
are.

00:56:48.479 --> 00:56:52.939
So those are all fantastic tools and you know
in the summertime I keep liquid nitrogen around

00:56:52.939 --> 00:56:56.660
because my daughter and I love to make instant
ice cream or we'll buy fruit on the way home

00:56:56.660 --> 00:56:58.519
and say, "Hey, let's make sorbet out of that."

00:56:58.519 --> 00:56:59.849
And you know liquid nitrogen's cheap.

00:56:59.849 --> 00:57:02.420
There's a place up the street, I live near
a hospital, I can get the stuff cheap and

00:57:02.420 --> 00:57:04.420
we pour it on all kinds of stuff.

00:57:04.420 --> 00:57:08.130
Some times we soak crackers in liquid nitrogen
and give them to the dogs, which is really

00:57:08.130 --> 00:57:11.989
cool because as the dog chews the cracker,
the steam shoots out of their mouth.

00:57:11.989 --> 00:57:12.989
[laughter]

00:57:12.989 --> 00:57:17.039
&gt;&gt;Alton Brown: But I'm not sure that's legal,
so I, I don't know how to do that.

00:57:17.039 --> 00:57:22.250
And, and I use xanthan gum to keep my, my
dressings stable.

00:57:22.250 --> 00:57:23.479
So I use these things.

00:57:23.479 --> 00:57:29.930
I use you know occasionally we'll use a tapioca
maltodextrin to turn olive oil into a powder

00:57:29.930 --> 00:57:31.819
because that's fun and I can put it on stuff.

00:57:31.819 --> 00:57:33.970
But by and large they're all just tools.

00:57:33.970 --> 00:57:38.829
And when an artist becomes defined by the
tools, that's a problem, in general.

